While I certainly do applaud her initiative and wanting to contribute to the effort to eventually prevent this COVID-19 virus from creating this level of pandemic, remember that there are thousands of people like her who volunteer for clinical trials all the time when a new drug is tested. She is participating in a phase I trial, which is healthy volunteers, to test the safety of the vaccine and determine maximum safe dosage as well as monitor any potential side effects.  After many months of data collection and analysis, if it is safe for human use with minimum adverse effects, they will move to Phase II, consisting of a much larger sample of patients who are actually sick, to measure the efficacy of the vaccine, again for many months. This is the regulatory process for all new drugs, including vaccines, to make sure it is generally safe and delivers the desired patient outcomes.  The approval process can also take some time as all the clinical and safety data needs to be reviewed and proven before they move forward to introduce it on the market.  So while that happens, we need to keep ourselves healthy, hygienic and following guidelines shared by health professionals and regulatory officials.
